data.text:
Conceptual illustration of a fully integrated photonic architecture to
compute convolutional operations. An on-chip laser (not used here) pumps an
integrated Si3N4 microresonator to generate a broadband soliton frequency
comb. Individual comb teeth, which form the input vectors, are modulated at
high speeds, multiplied with a matrix of non-volatile phase-change memory
cells, and summed along each column on a photodetector
